<p><b>Human Rights Council 
Twenty-sixth session 
</b>Agenda items 3 and 5 
<b>Promotion and protection of all human rights, civil,  
political, economic, social and cultural rights,  
including the right to development  
</b></p>
<p><b>Human rights bodies and mechanisms 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Summary of discussions of the Forum on Business and 
Human Rights 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Note by the Secretariat</b>*<b> 
</b></p>
<p> In accordance with Human Rights Council resolution 17/4, the Forum on Business 
and Human Rights was held in Geneva from 2 to 4 December 2013. The Forum was 
chaired by Makarim Wibisono, and held under the guidance of the Working Group on the 
issue of human rights and transnational corporations and other business enterprises. The 
Chairperson of the Forum prepared a summary of the discussions of the Forum 
(A/HRC/FBHR/2013/4). The Working Group reflected on the proceedings of the Forum 
and made recommendations thereon addressed to States, business enterprises and other 
stakeholders in its report to the Human Rights Council (A/HRC/26/25). 
</p>
<p>    
</p>
